>not anonymous at all
It's more anonymous than 4chan where all tor exit nodes are banned and everyone posts with their real IP.

>store CP on your hard-drive
You know perfectly well what content you're seeding. Don't like a board? Don't join it. Don't like an image someone posted? Mute it. Problem solved.

>slow and consume a lot of bandwidth
It works perfectly fine for me

>clearly a honey pot
Of course it is, accuse one of the few opensource alternatives we have. Good thing clearnet chans are totally not compromised, never cooperate with the authorities and hand over sensitive data.

>You need to config a shit tons of shit just to lurk
Download a python script, configure it with tor and lurk ahead. If that's too complicated for you then maybe you should head back to reddit or wherever you came from
